<p><b>Per Brinch Hansen</b> (November 13, 1938 – July 31, 2007) was a <a href="/wiki/Denmark" title="Denmark">Danish</a>-<a href="/wiki/United_States" title="United States">American</a> <a href="/wiki/Computer_scientist" title="Computer scientist">computer scientist</a> known for his work in <a href="/wiki/Operating_system" title="Operating system">operating systems</a>, <a href="/wiki/Concurrent_computing" title="Concurrent computing">concurrent programming</a> and <a href="/wiki/Parallel_computing" title="Parallel computing">parallel</a> and <a href="/wiki/Distributed_computing" title="Distributed computing">distributed computing</a>.</p>
<p></p>
